  {"a":"twitch_bot","b":"ziggs","win":["Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch","Twitch"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You out-trade Ziggs in this window because his Bouncing Bomb is a skillshot that only hits waves, not you weaving through minions; sit on Deadly Venom stacks from the brush and Expunge him the moment he steps up to Q the caster minions, since his Satchel Charge is his only escape and it's often on cooldown."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Spray and Pray plus Ambush opens from stealth well inside his poke range; Ziggs has no reliable self-peel besides a single Satchel knockback, so a clean flank with support CC blows him up before he can Minefield-zone or W away."},{"when":"1st item","text":"A completed Terminus or Runaan's makes your stacked Expunge a one-shot on his squishy immobile frame; Ziggs relies on chip poke that your venom regen and lifesteal shrug off, so your all-in breakpoint massively outpaces his."},{"when":"Late","text":"In fights you delete him with Rat-Ta-Tat-Tat before his long-cast Bombs matter, as long as you flank from stealth and don't eat a full Minefield plus Mega Inferno Bomb; space behind your frontline and pick your angle, and his lack of mobility makes him free."}],"wants":{"you":["Weaving through minions to dodge Bouncing Bomb then Expunging on his walk-up","Flanking from Ambush past his poke range","Punishing his Satchel Charge cooldown to all-in"],"foe":["Landing Bouncing Bomb poke and zoning waves with Minefield","Using Satchel Charge to knock you away or reposition","Chipping you from max range to deny your walk-up"]},"early":"At Levels 1-2 you weave behind minions to avoid Ziggs's Bouncing Bomb while dropping Deadly Venom stacks whenever he steps to farm; his short-fuse Q struggles to hit a moving target, so his poke is far less reliable than it looks and you control the tempo.","mid":"From 3 to 6 you own the lane: your stacked Expunge out-bursts his chip poke, his Satchel Charge is his only escape and easily baited, and your Level 6 stealth all-in ignores his lack of self-peel; force him off the wave and punish every walk-up.","late":"Post-item you spike faster than his poke can ever matter and your spread DPS shreds his immobile squishy body in any fight you open from stealth, so just respect the odd Minefield-plus-ult zone and pick your flank angle before committing.","whys":["Level 1 favours you because weaving through minions denies his Bouncing Bomb while venom chips his walk-up.","Level 2 stays yours as your reliable poke beats his skillshot-dependent farm harass.","Level 3 is yours once a full Expunge out-bursts his chip poke.","Levels 4-5 favour you as Deadly Venom stacks punish every step he takes to farm.","Level 6 is yours because a stealth all-in ignores his single-Satchel self-peel.","First item favours you since your Terminus/Runaan's Expunge one-shots his immobile squishy frame.","Two-plus items stays yours as your spread DPS shreds him before his long-cast bombs land."]}
